WEBVTT

00:01.935 --> 00:04.569
Well, this is so depressing.

00:04.638 --> 00:06.649
What are you talking about?
It's Central Park.

00:06.673 --> 00:08.306
A-All these cute little boats...

00:08.375 --> 00:10.386
Yeah, and it's a beautiful day,
but the only reason we're here

00:10.410 --> 00:12.210
is 'cause a dead body was found.

00:12.279 --> 00:13.845
You need a vacation, Reagan.

00:13.914 --> 00:15.224
Probably find
a dead body there, too.

00:15.248 --> 00:16.848
Good morning, Detectives.

00:16.917 --> 00:19.183
- Not according to him.
- Uh...

00:19.252 --> 00:20.086
What do we got?

00:20.087 --> 00:22.120
Purse was tossed aside,
I.D. on the ground

00:22.188 --> 00:24.122
says her name
is Jessica King, age 29.

00:24.190 --> 00:26.190
Kid over there
found her, then promptly

00:26.259 --> 00:27.307
threw up his
Froot Loops.

00:27.308 --> 00:28.138
Poor little guy.

00:28.162 --> 00:29.895
Tough way to start
the day at any age.

00:29.896 --> 00:31.930
Thanks.

00:33.366 --> 00:34.966
I'm not seeing
any scratches

00:35.035 --> 00:36.534
or signs of
a struggle.

00:36.603 --> 00:38.080
She probably didn't even
see it coming.

00:38.104 --> 00:39.737
Single stab wound to the heart.

00:39.806 --> 00:41.284
You think that's a
message of some sort

00:41.308 --> 00:42.574
or just a lucky shot?

00:42.642 --> 00:43.942
Lucky for who?

00:44.010 --> 00:45.610
I don't know.

00:45.679 --> 00:48.513
That's what we'll have
to find out.

00:54.187 --> 00:56.120
Gramps? Hello?

00:56.189 --> 00:57.755
In here.

00:57.824 --> 01:00.491
Chemistry book you forgot
is there on the table.

01:00.560 --> 01:02.104
- What are you doing down there?
- Uh, the sink trap

01:02.128 --> 01:04.162
needed fixing.

01:04.230 --> 01:07.065
Hey, did you see a box
on the porch when you came in?

01:07.133 --> 01:08.253
No. You expecting something?

01:08.301 --> 01:10.068
Yeah.
Nicky's graduation present.

01:10.136 --> 01:11.069
A locket of Betty's

01:11.137 --> 01:12.770
that she's always loved.

01:12.839 --> 01:15.106
Clasp was broken,
so I sent it away to get fixed.

01:15.175 --> 01:17.286
It's supposed to be delivered
this morning.

01:17.310 --> 01:19.410
- Is that you or me?
- Not me.

01:23.416 --> 01:25.783
Ha. Speak of the devil.

01:25.852 --> 01:28.319
All right, help me up.

01:28.388 --> 01:30.622
According to the text,
the thing was just delivered.

01:30.690 --> 01:32.957
- I can go run out and grab it.
- No, no, no.

01:33.026 --> 01:35.093
At my age, when you commit
to standing up,

01:35.161 --> 01:36.761
you have to see it through.

01:38.000 --> 01:44.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:45.205 --> 01:47.105
Van's long gone.

01:47.173 --> 01:50.475
So where the hell's my package?

01:50.543 --> 01:52.644
It didn't
just disappear.

01:52.712 --> 01:54.812
You ever hear of porch pirates?

01:54.881 --> 01:56.814
Maybe somebody
stole it.

02:05.592 --> 02:07.236
- Reagan.
- Oh, thank God.

02:07.260 --> 02:08.916
I didn't know if you'd answer.

02:09.604 --> 02:10.571
Who's this?

02:10.783 --> 02:13.018
It's Armin Janko, Eddie's dad.

02:13.700 --> 02:16.634
Please don't hang up.

02:16.703 --> 02:19.270
Uh, you can't be out yet,
Mr. Janko.

02:19.339 --> 02:21.639
No, not for another
three to five.

02:21.708 --> 02:22.874
But I need to talk to you.

02:22.942 --> 02:24.208
Okay, talk.

02:24.277 --> 02:25.143
In person.

02:25.211 --> 02:26.778
I promise it's nothing bad.

02:26.846 --> 02:28.324
It's just something
I would rather discuss

02:28.348 --> 02:30.415
with my soon-to-be
son-in-law in person.

02:30.483 --> 02:32.450
Do me that one favor?

02:33.553 --> 02:35.520
Okay. Yeah.

02:35.588 --> 02:37.055
And don't tell my daughter.

02:37.123 --> 02:38.389
That's two favors.

02:38.458 --> 02:40.058
You can tell her soon,

02:40.126 --> 02:41.726
just come and hear me out first.

02:42.829 --> 02:45.430
All right, you got it.

02:45.498 --> 02:47.432
Bye.

02:56.976 --> 03:00.211
Just for the record, I think
asking her up here is a mistake.

03:00.280 --> 03:02.130
If there was a record,
you'd be on it.

03:02.131 --> 03:04.749
He's right, boss. All due
respect, I cannot imagine

03:04.818 --> 03:06.084
what you're thinking here.

03:06.152 --> 03:08.319
Sometimes a problem
is more manageable

03:08.388 --> 03:10.054
if you engage it from the top.

03:15.128 --> 03:17.895
Last chance to walk this back.

03:18.998 --> 03:21.432
Let's have her.

03:37.083 --> 03:38.850
Professor.

03:38.918 --> 03:41.719
Commissioner Moore,
Lieutenant Gormley.

03:41.788 --> 03:43.788
We've met.

03:45.525 --> 03:47.792
Have a seat.

03:53.833 --> 03:56.467
So we're looking at five
assaults on illegal immigrants

03:56.536 --> 03:59.871
allegedly committed
by an NYPD officer.

03:59.939 --> 04:01.606
Five, right?

04:01.674 --> 04:03.307
So far.

04:03.376 --> 04:05.943
And you're claiming
the exact same pattern

04:06.012 --> 04:09.413
in each of the five assaults?
- Yes.

04:09.482 --> 04:11.349
He show a shield
and an I.D. card?

04:11.417 --> 04:12.417
Every time.

04:12.485 --> 04:14.585
And verbally
identified himself

04:14.654 --> 04:15.898
as a New York City
police officer?

04:15.922 --> 04:18.122
Why do I feel like you're trying
to trip me up?

04:18.190 --> 04:20.158
No, we're just trying
to ascertain the facts.

04:20.226 --> 04:21.625
And balance them
against the fact

04:21.694 --> 04:24.162
that you have falsely accused
this department before.

04:24.230 --> 04:26.964
What possible agenda
could I have here?

04:27.033 --> 04:30.768
Well, that's what they call
the known unknown.

04:32.872 --> 04:36.040
The only known unknown here
is which cop.

04:40.580 --> 04:42.180
Tell me something.

04:42.248 --> 04:45.416
Are all the crimes in this city
committed by cops?

04:47.420 --> 04:51.656
Just setting the table
for the meal I'm expecting.

04:51.724 --> 04:55.393
Anonymous accusations
are difficult to investigate

04:55.461 --> 04:57.728
and even harder to prosecute.

04:57.797 --> 05:00.097
And that's not stonewalling you,
it's a fact.

05:00.166 --> 05:02.633
And it's why I convinced them
to give their names,

05:02.702 --> 05:05.369
addresses, phone numbers.

05:05.438 --> 05:07.605
We'll look into it.

05:08.708 --> 05:10.041
That's it?

05:10.109 --> 05:12.577
It will be investigated
thoroughly.

05:12.645 --> 05:15.346
That's what we do here.
Thanks for coming up.

05:22.755 --> 05:26.290
Your granddaughter Nicky
is a lovely young woman.

05:27.961 --> 05:30.228
You know my granddaughter?

05:30.296 --> 05:33.898
As does the Justice Coalition
board now.

05:35.635 --> 05:37.568
A job interview.

05:40.773 --> 05:42.039
First you've heard?

05:43.376 --> 05:46.210
And wondering
why you're letting me know.

05:47.313 --> 05:49.647
Gentlemen.

05:54.220 --> 05:56.487
Son of a bitch.

05:58.591 --> 06:02.591
